The driver &amp; the young girl&#8217;s mother were also killed when a minibus taxi collided with a bus on the N1 near Beaufort West. CAPE TOWN - A six-year-old girl has died in an accident on the N1 between Beaufort West and Leeu Gamka.The taxi driver and the child s mother also died in the crash at around 4am on Thursday morning.Emergency Medical Services spokesperson Robert Daniels says a minibus taxi collided with a bus about 50 kilometres from Beaufort West. Eight others were seriously injured and ten more suffered minor injuries. All patients were rushed to Beaufort West Provincial Hospital by Emergency Medical Services. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)